        ┌────────── MPU6050 ──────────┐
        │                              │
        │   VCC  ─────────── 3.3V      │
        │   GND  ─────────── GND       │
ESP32   │   SCL  ─────────── GPIO 22   │
Board   │   SDA  ─────────── GPIO 21   │
        │                              │
        └──────────────────────────────┘
                
                ┌──── Buttons ────┐
                │                 │
                │ Left Button     │ Right Button
                │                 │
GPIO 19 ────────┘                 └──────────── GPIO 5
(each button: other pin to GND, internal pull-up enabled)


| Component    | Pin       | Connects To | Notes                 |
| ------------ | --------- | ----------- | --------------------- |
| MPU6050      | VCC       | 3.3V        | **Do not use 5V**     |
| MPU6050      | GND       | GND         | Common ground         |
| MPU6050      | SCL       | GPIO 22     | I2C Clock             |
| MPU6050      | SDA       | GPIO 21     | I2C Data              |
| Left Button  | One pin   | GPIO 19     | Left Click / Drag     |
| Left Button  | Other pin | GND         | Uses internal pull-up |
| Right Button | One pin   | GPIO 5      | Right Click           |
| Right Button | Other pin | GND         | Debounced             |


ESP32 USB 5V → onboard regulator → 3.3V supply
MPU6050 must be powered from 3.3V
